## Implementation Timeline

### Phase 1: Problem Diagnosis (T+0 to T+25-30 min)

#### 1.1 Data Loading & Metric Computation
- [ ] **Load ad data**: headline, description, keywords, segment, placement, impressions, CTR, CPC, CVR, qualified_rate
- [ ] **Compute business-native metrics** (per segment × placement):
  ```python
  # Core business KPIs
  QPI = CTR × CVR × qualified_rate    # Quality per impression
  CPQL = CPC / (CVR × qualified_rate) # Cost per qualified lead
  ```
- [ ] **Fast sanity checks**:
  - Filter: impressions ≥ 500 (stable samples)
  - Use segment medians & quartiles (no heavy significance tests)

#### 1.2 Root Cause Identification with Evidence
- [ ] **Copy-Intent Mismatch Detection**:
  ```python
  # Identify low QPI/CTR on specific keyword themes
  mismatch_evidence = df[
      (df['QPI'] < df.groupby('segment')['QPI'].transform('quantile', 0.25)) &
      (df['impressions'] >= 1000)  # High impression, low performance
  ]
  ```
- [ ] **Qualification Gap Analysis**:
```python
  # OK CTR but high CPQL (weak benefit/CTA clarity)
  qualification_issues = df[
      (df['CTR'] >= df.groupby('segment')['CTR'].transform('median')) &
      (df['CPQL'] >= df.groupby('segment')['CPQL'].transform('quantile', 0.75))
  ]
  ```

#### 1.3 Optional Fatigue Detection
- [ ] **Fatigue flag**: 7-day CTR ≤ 80% of first-3-day CTR (if date data available)

#### Deliverable: 1-2 root causes with 2-3 evidence rows each

